Very fresh. They pride themselves on freshness. Be sure to eat here. They are amazing. The taste, the service, the people. < Review>
Ahmed is a magician with the scissors!

I'm originally from New York and after moving to Irvine in 2018, finding a barber wasn't easy.

The cheap barber for $25 will cut your hair in 5-10 mins. A $40 haircut from supercuts or Danckut's is inconsistent because the barber keeps changing and overall not worth the price.

Ahmed's consistent haircut is high quality for only $35! I usually leave with a good tip because he does such a good job!

What attracted me to his shop was the 100+ positive yelp reviews. What kept me coming back was the confidence boost I get from a haircut from Tesoro.

He knows exactly how to style my hair without needing lots of details. After a while, I just ask for the usual and it comes out perfect every time.

Ahmed is a one man show and for good reason. No one can do a better job than this craftsman!

If you're in the Orange county area you MUST visit this man and see the transformation happen before your eyes!< /Review>

<username>Private Customer</username><Time>1553930823038< /Time><Rate>3</Rate><review>I think the owner, who is the barber, is a very personable person. It was a bit too "personable" for me, although it is better than your average retaining tactics, it is a better form.

I appreciate form. Regardless, good nature and friendliness should never substitute expertise, and boundaries, which on those two, there was a subtle lack.

I called for an appointment, I asked for a time and price, I was quote $30.

I had two pictures with me, but the length of the cut was shorter than on the picture, and the style wasn't what it shows.

I then asked him for a specific cut that is at the length it was, it was a familiar cut for me, and I have been to several locations for it. I know how long, and how many tries it should take for it to be done on skill levels. It took several communications to get close to this basic cut. I'm still going to have to go elsewhere to have it cleaned up a bit.

The entire appointment has already taken some time to complete the cut (despite his talking), and that, was brought up to me when I visited the next night to pay him in cash.

This shop doesn't accept credit cards. I hesitate using checks. It was late and so the decision was to pay him in cash the next day.

He gave me back $5 without me mentioning the price difference when I went back, I gave him back the $5 questioning him why.  I didn't see the price list until now.

I was invited to a demonstration of using wax, which I thought was nice of him. It was a brief rinse, semi-dry and the demonstration of wax over gel. There was also offerings of a string scraping thing for a facial hair found on me. Very nice of him, however expertise and professionalism will win over any gesture, that is, for me, every single time, in a business transaction.<//review>< Pictures>

<Review>Excellent experience! Alex was right on time. He was honest and very professional. He did his job and explained quickly and efficiently. I would highly recommend Brody Pennell for any AC services. Thank you Alex!</Review><GmapID>0x80c2b97e9fc3ce67:0x9ac827d6e7cba772</GmapID><Time>1618518588805</Time></record></dataset><record>
<Rating>5</Rating>< text>
Experienced, knowledgable, trustworthy and Professional, from the sales visit, pre-walk through with the project manager to the installation.  Brody Pennell replaced an existing 1982 2 ton Day and Night HVAC unit with a new Carrier 3 ton unit. Additionally, they installed new exposed ducting with two additional registers and an additional return to accommodate the larger HVAC unit.  I was very impressed with the attention to detail and efforts to meet my needs and expectations.  The finished result and look is amazing.

When selecting a proposal, I am not necessarily looking for the lowest or cheapest bid.  I am more interested in the best quality, value and professional workmanship for a fair reasonable price. Do it once, do it right.  The job also required a crane to remove the old HVAC unit and deliver the new unit on the roof 4 floors up.  It also required scaffolding inside the condo unit and cutting through the exterior and interior walls to add the new ducting and return.

I live in an 1173 square foot condo unit with an upstairs loft space which has a 19' foot ceiling in the main living area.  The previous HVAC system did not deliver air to the upper loft area which I frequently use as a guest space. As a result, the upper loft area has always been 10 or more degrees warmer than the main level making it very uncomfortable during the summer months.  The entire space is now evenly cooled throughout and very comfortable.  The new 3 ton unit works effortlessly to cool the space and runs only a fraction of the time that the previous unit did.  Additionally, they made every effort to mitigate and reduce the noise and vibration.  I do not hear a sound when it is running and only can tell that it is running when feeling the cool air circulating throughout.

I also want to mention that Brody Pennell was the last to service my previous HVAC unit over 10 years ago which was going strong until recently.  Once again, Experienced, knowledgable, trustworthy and Professional.  Highly Recommended.<//text>

<resp>{'time': 1558818221453, 'text': 'Thank you Hamish for telling your story.  We sincerely appreciate you.'}</resp>< text>
The True Measure of a Contractor

It‚Äôs easy to give a company high marks when everything goes smoothly. But let‚Äôs face it, sometimes things don‚Äôt go smoothly. And the true measure of a contractor is revealed in how they respond when things go wrong. Brody Pennell simply sets the standard that all others should aspire to.

In a nutshell, my wife and I hired these wonderful human beings to do a major job at our townhouse: replacing the 30-year-old rooftop HVAC unit with a new, energy efficient one. Of course, before choosing them, we did our due diligence, secured four different bids and read all the reviews, etc.

Brody‚Äôs was certainly not the least expensive estimate we received. But they also weren‚Äôt the most expensive. (Those guys who have the fancy retro graphics on their trucks were the most expensive‚Ä¶ and yet their rep did not offer us the better equipment options that Brody did, he was slow to follow up, and just didn‚Äôt seem to care about winning our business.) And on the flipside, there was a contractor whose bid came in much cheaper. But he suggested that getting a permit for a major crane operation over a public sidewalk on a shared-property condominium building should be considered optional ‚Äì giant red flag.

In addition to having great reviews and a reasonable price, our interactions with Brody‚Äôs rep, Brian, were great. He was extremely knowledgeable, ridiculously responsive and just gave off good vibes. So we happily went with Brody Pennell and are so glad we did. They sent out their foreman, Jaime ‚Äì another kind, courteous, professional man ‚Äì to scout the job, got it scheduled quickly, even though it was around the Thanksgiving holiday, and showed up exactly when they said they would with every visit. The big installation itself went swimmingly. And again the Brody techs that did the bulk of the work were great representatives for the company.

Then, after the work was complete, a couple of problems revealed themselves. I won‚Äôt go into extreme detail on this. But due to the custom curb mounting that the new machine required, there was an increase in vibrations into the house, which was unexpected from a new, more efficient machine. And there was a roof leak issue that occurred during the unprecedented rains that we had last winter.

For both issues, Brody was on their game without us having to push them. They were simply committed to making things right for us from the beginning. The head of the company, Mike Carson, dealt with us directly, every step of the way. And the entire Brody team did everything in their power to get the issues fixed. This required several visits to the house, and sourcing subcontractors to deal with certain issues. To be clear, this wasn‚Äôt convenient for either us or them. And Brody likely ended up losing money on this job. But that never stopped them from doing what they needed to in order to make things right.

That is what separates a great contractor from a serviceable one. And that is why we will be customers of theirs for life and will always recommend Brody Pennell to anyone who needs HVAC work done.</text>

< Review>
**UPDATE:  was contacted about a week later by president mike carson regarding my air conditioning service.  he agreed with my review, but disputed the amount of time the worker was at my house (1.5 hours vs the actual ~20 minutes).  i understand that the worker can put whatever time he likes on his forms, maybe even include travel time even though their office is about 2 miles from my house. but i took time off from work that morning to let him in and out of my house and i did not miss 1.5 hours of work that day.  we agreed to disagree.

mr. carson offered a partial refund of ~$160 which brought the labor costs closer to other competitors, though he stated that he could not match khan air conditioning, probably because their overhead is lower due to being located in the valley.  so $440 compared to khan's $375 for a WARRANTY-COVERED REPAIR ...

i appreciate mr. carson's attempt to reach out to me.  i also appreciate the power of google plus to inform business owners and supervisors of ways to provide a level of service that is satisfactory to their customers.

however, i am disappointed that it required a truthful negative review on a review site to get a less unsatisfactory response.

**PREVIOUS REVIEW:  TLDR -- I regret choosing Brody Pennell to perform warranty service on my air conditioner.

in a house built brand new in 2014, the brand new carrier ac stopped blowing air ...  literally 1 year and 2 months -- just outside primary warranty coverage ... but still within the 5 year parts warranty ...

found brody pennell (among others) on the carrier website and every company i called wanted to charge ~$100 just to diagnose the issue ... none would apply the $100 to future work which means if you got a second or third opinion, you'd be out $100-$200 without any work being done ...

brody pennell was able to come out the quickest and diagnosed the faulty blower motor covered under warranty ... then quoted a MIND-BLOWING ~$600 for labor/incidentals ... i called to ask for some kind of consideration, but the operator suggested that he couldn't do anything unless i had a maintenance plan (~$200/yr) with them ...

so my dilemma was to take a chance with brody pennell since i was already in for a non-refundable ~$100 with the guess that other companies would charge the non-refundable $100 and also be in the same ballpark with labor charges ...

so the part was ordered and the repairman came and fixed the motor in LITERALLY 20 MINUTES -- 8am to 8:20am ... unscrew/unplug bad part, re-plug/re-screw good part, done ... $600 for 20 minutes of work on a warranty-covered part ...

brody pennell gave no consideration to the age of the unit (only a year old) or the amount of time to fix the motor (plug and play in 20 minutes) ...

horrible guess on my part ...

turns out 2 of my neighbors also have failed blower motors (apparently carrier ac units are horrible and will fail just outside of 1 year of moderate use) and they took a chance on other companies' labor charges ...

khan air conditioning charged my neighbor $375 for THE EXACT SAME WORK ...

please do yourself a favor and use khan air conditioning or ANYONE ELSE THAT CHARGES LESS THAN $600 FOR 20 MINUTES WORTH OF WORK ...

PS -- sent an e-mail to corporate carrier regarding the extremely high labor cost on a warranty-covered part ... the response:

"Each dealer is independently owned and operated and we do not control their business practices."<//Review>

< review>
I use the lake almost daily to exercise my dogs. First week of Jan. 2021 was at Wrinkle Cove boat ramp and found a camera. It is a Cannon Power Shot Elph 180. Checked SD card trying to find an ID. Looked like a out of town family on a cross country trip with most of the shots of two young girls. If it is yours I left contact info with park rangers and camp host at entrance.</review>

Ricky Hallowes<//username>
<UserId.>110189394722084385454<//UserId.><gmapID>0x8090844fea48cb3b:0x55a3df78222706ea</gmapID><pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMf5BceymDHyZnG6hYhY7f01Kjnp7arrAjXZmgy=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//pics><Rate>5<//Rate><Resp>None<//Resp><time>1610478939834< /time></record></dataset><record>
< user_id>
104056413164156146314</user_id>
< user_name>
Joshua Martinez</user_name>
< Time>
1565099500991< /Time>
< Rating>
4</Rating>
< review>
We spent the day here for our first time and had a good experience. We didn't go in all the way to the camp sites but we stopped at the first right turn which has parking spots about 100' away from the water that are blocked with huge rocks to prevent vehicle access. There are about 3 over heads with tables as well as bbq pits up near the road. The water is perfect temperature, not to cold and not to warm. Bring water shoes though, it is very rocky in the water as well as on land so don't forget your chairs. Also bring some kind of canopy for shade since there aren't any trees anywhere near the water. It wasn't to busy either where we were which was awesome.</review>

<date>1578904720051<//date>< Review>
When I first heard of New Hogan Lake all I could think about was the fishing, the being out in the nature and well for me it was kind of a belated celebration. Yes for me going somewhere where one haven't been before should be an adventure, wouldn't you think?  Anyway for this place for me was kindof a fantasy in some ways. Even though the fishing was great, the camping with friends and the enjoyment of sharing of ood over a camp fire with rhat open air of conversation with those campers next door to us. But the biggest thing that I came to notice wasn't just the nature or natural surroundings of all things was the mere fact of how  many couples that were there. As I scoped around and to my own amazement I sensed certain romance to this place. The rolling hills coming to this area. The presence of an eternal peace I felt from within. Further looking into the softness of the countryside and the soft flow of the sunset. It seemed magical in ways that I couldn't imagine in other places. Granted its my own opinion but you must experience taking part in visiting New Hogan Lake. A place to take the family, a good friend or perhaps that certain "Love" on a short stroll through that's making it's calling. So when and if you do go, share it, I think its well worth it.<//Review>

<name>TonJala Mack< /name>< Date>
1534277731558<//Date>
< rating>
1</rating>
< Text>
We booked sites 77 and 78 at the Acorn Campground for our family camping trip.
The lake is beautiful and the grounds are nice  but OMG THE WASPS WERE RELENTLESS AND EVERYWHERE!!!  We couldn't even eat or drink anything because the moment you open food or drink, here they come and you literally cannot get away from them.  My son and my grand daughters ate dinner in the car, while my daughter-in-law and myself just opted not to eat after finding out that there was no where to go to get away from the wasps.  We anxiously awaited the coming of evening so that the wasps would go away,  only to find out that after the wasps went in, the frogs came out in numbers.  They literally ran in packs, and though no one was really afraid of them, it is unnerving to have 5 to 10 jump out of nowhere with each and every step, and to find 20 to 30 surrounding each tree, bush, water faucet, etc.

Don't misunderstand.  We camp every year as a family, and are not looking to be bug and critter free.  The conditions at New Hogan Lake, however, were quite extreme.  The lady who manages the campsites told us that we have to remember that the wasps and frogs are in their home.  Though this is very true, it is up to those who manage the campsites to inform patrons of the presence of the wasps and frogs before a person makes their reservation so that decisions can be made with everything in mind.  We had a person with a bee allergy (though minor) as part of our group.  One sting, though an issue, is not life threatening, but there existed the possibility of multiple stings which would have been detrimental because the wasps were just that brutal.  We visited the campground in March before booking it and spoke with the host about the sites.  Had we, at that time, been informed of the possibility that the wasps would be rampaging like this as this is their home, we would have looked for other sites within the campground where the wasps weren't so prevalent, or opted for another campground all together.  And for her to say that we may or may not get a refund because we didn't want to stay there makes me NOT A FAN OF NEW HOGAN LAKE!!!!</Text>

Needless to say, I was annoyed. Then I found out that AAA members can do vehicle transfers at AAA branches (Not sure why I didn't think of that before...). I went in, and within 20 minutes, they helped me complete my vehicle transfer. It took the DMV over 9 months to do what AAA took less than 20 minutes to do. Update:

The staff at the DMV services counter have made many improvements, including the triage of long lines to best route patrons and customer service focused one on one communication. I went in thru drive thru and the lady got my order down and even asked me if everything on the screen was correct and I looked at it for about a minute and said yes.
